51.9	Things_Fall_Apart	Things Fall Apart	Things Fall Apart is an English-language novel by Nigerian author Chinua Achebe published in 1958. It is seen as the archetypal modern African novel in English, and one of the first African novels written in English to receive global critical acclaim. It is a staple book in schools throughout Africa and widely read and studied in English-speaking countries around the world. The title of the novel comes from William Butler Yeats's poem "The Second Coming".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/65/ThingsFallApart.jpg/201px-ThingsFallApart.jpg
